Pliny ſays, the Chief City of Nubia was Tenupſus;
Antient chief City. but the latter and more modern Writers give the Priority to Kondari; Leo Africanus makes Dangala the Metropolis, which he ſays containeth near ten thouſand Houſes, but very meanly built; and that all the reſt are poor Villages and Hamlets ſcattered about the Nyle. The Natives of this Countrey,

   Nubian Geographers. who have left us ſome Deſcriptions thereof, affirm Nubia the Principal; and the others pretending to any Eminency, Nubie, Kuſa, Ghalva, Dankala, Jalak and Sala.

